# Security Conventions

## Input Validation & XSS Prevention

### Data Validation & Sanitization

- Validate all inputs on client and server side
- Sanitize HTML content to prevent XSS attacks
- Use Content Security Policy headers

```typescript
// ✅ Input validation & XSS prevention
import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';

// Basic validation functions
export const createTrail = async (data: CreateTrailData) => {
  const { name, description, difficulty, distance, elevationGain } = data;

  if (
    !name ||
    !description ||
    !difficulty ||
    !distance ||
    elevationGain === undefined
  ) {
    throw { message: 'Faltan campos requeridos', statusCode: 400 };
  }

  if (
    typeof name !== 'string' ||
    typeof description !== 'string' ||
    typeof difficulty !== 'string' ||
    typeof distance !== 'number' ||
    typeof elevationGain !== 'number'
  ) {
    throw { message: 'Formato de campos inválido', statusCode: 400 };
  }

  if (name.length < 3 || name.length > 100) {
    throw {
      message: 'El nombre debe tener entre 3 y 100 caracteres',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }

  if (!/^[a-zA-ZáéíóúÁÉÍÓÚñÑ\s]+$/.test(name)) {
    throw {
      message: 'El nombre solo puede contener letras y espacios',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }

  if (description.length < 10 || description.length > 1000) {
    throw {
      message: 'La descripción debe tener entre 10 y 1000 caracteres',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }

  const validDifficulties = ['fácil', 'moderado', 'difícil', 'experto'];
  if (!validDifficulties.includes(difficulty)) {
    throw {
      message: 'La dificultad debe ser: fácil, moderado, difícil o experto',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }

  if (distance <= 0 || distance > 100) {
    throw {
      message:
        'La distancia debe ser un número positivo y no puede exceder 100 km',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }

  if (elevationGain < 0 || elevationGain > 5000) {
    throw {
      message:
        'El desnivel no puede ser negativo y no puede exceder 5000 metros',
      statusCode: 400,
    };
  }
};

// Validation middleware
const validateTrailInputMiddleware = (
  req: Request,
  res: Response,
  next: NextFunction,
) => {
  try {
    createTrail(req.body);
    next();
  } catch (error: any) {
    return res.status(error.statusCode || 400).json({ error: error.message });
  }
};

// XSS prevention
const sanitizeHtml = (html: string): string => {
  return DOMPurify.sanitize(html, {
    ALLOWED_TAGS: ['b', 'i', 'em', 'strong', 'p', 'br'],
    ALLOWED_ATTR: [],
  });
};

// Security headers
const setSecurityHeaders = (
  req: Request,
  res: Response,
  next: NextFunction,
) => {
  res.setHeader(
    'Content-Security-Policy',
    "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; connect-src 'self'",
  );
  res.setHeader('X-Frame-Options', 'DENY');
  res.setHeader('X-Content-Type-Options', 'nosniff');
  res.setHeader('Referrer-Policy', 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin');
  next();
};
```

## API Security

### Rate Limiting & CORS

- Implement rate limiting with different limits for different endpoints
- Configure CORS with specific origins (no wildcards in production)
- Log suspicious activity

```typescript
// ✅ Rate limiting & CORS
import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';
import cors from 'cors';

// Rate limiting
const createRateLimit = (windowMs: number, max: number, message: string) => {
  return rateLimit({
    windowMs,
    max,
    message: { error: message },
    standardHeaders: true,
    legacyHeaders: false,
    handler: (req, res) =>
      res
        .status(429)
        .json({ error: message, retryAfter: Math.round(windowMs / 1000) }),
  });
};

const authRateLimit = createRateLimit(
  15 * 60 * 1000,
  5,
  'Demasiados intentos de autenticación. Inténtalo de nuevo en 15 minutos.',
);
const apiRateLimit = createRateLimit(
  15 * 60 * 1000,
  100,
  'Demasiadas solicitudes. Inténtalo de nuevo más tarde.',
);

// CORS configuration
const corsOptions = {
  origin: (
    origin: string | undefined,
    callback: (err: Error | null, allow?: boolean) => void,
  ) => {
    const allowedOrigins = [
      'http://localhost:3000',
      'https://trailrunningcal.com',
      'https://www.trailrunningcal.com',
    ];
    if (!origin || allowedOrigins.includes(origin)) callback(null, true);
    else callback(new Error('No permitido por CORS'));
  },
  credentials: true,
  methods: ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'DELETE', 'PATCH'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization', 'X-Requested-With'],
};
```

## Environment Variables & Secrets

### Secret Management & Configuration

- Never commit secrets to version control
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Validate required environment variables on startup
- Use different secrets for different environments

```typescript
// ✅ Environment variables & configuration
const requiredEnvVars = [
  'DATABASE_URL',
  'REDIS_URL',
  'EMAIL_SERVICE_API_KEY',
  'GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY',
];

const validateEnvironment = () => {
  const missingVars = requiredEnvVars.filter(
    (varName) => !process.env[varName],
  );
  if (missingVars.length > 0)
    throw new Error(
      `Missing required environment variables: ${missingVars.join(', ')}`,
    );
};

const config = {
  database: { url: process.env.DATABASE_URL! },
  redis: { url: process.env.REDIS_URL! },
  email: { apiKey: process.env.EMAIL_SERVICE_API_KEY! },
  maps: { apiKey: process.env.GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY! },
};
```

## Error Handling & Security Monitoring

### Secure Error Handling & Logging

- Don't expose sensitive information in error messages
- Log security events for monitoring and alerting
- Implement error boundaries for React components

```typescript
// ✅ Secure error handling & monitoring
interface SecurityEvent {
  type:
    | 'api_error'
    | 'validation_error'
    | 'file_upload_error'
    | 'suspicious_activity';
  ip: string;
  userAgent: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  details: Record<string, any>;
}

const handleApiError = (error: Error, req: Request, res: Response) => {
  console.error('API error:', {
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
    ip: req.ip,
    userAgent: req.get('User-Agent'),
    error: error.message,
  });
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Error interno del servidor' });
};

const logSecurityEvent = async (event: SecurityEvent) => {
  try {
    await SecurityLog.create({ ...event, timestamp: new Date() });
    if (event.type === 'suspicious_activity') await sendSecurityAlert(event);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to log security event:', error);
  }
};

// React error boundary
class SecurityErrorBoundary extends React.Component {
  constructor(props: any) {
    super(props);
    this.state = { hasError: false };
  }
  static getDerivedStateFromError(error: Error) {
    console.error('Security error boundary caught:', error);
    return { hasError: true };
  }
  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) {
      return (
        <div className="error-boundary">
          <h2>Error de Seguridad</h2>
          <p>
            Se ha detectado un problema de seguridad. Por favor, recarga la
            página.
          </p>
        </div>
      );
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}
```

## File Upload Security

### Secure File Handling

- Validate file types and sizes (5MB limit)
- Store files outside web root with secure filenames
- Scan uploaded files for malware

```typescript
// ✅ File upload security
import multer from 'multer';
import path from 'path';

const allowedMimeTypes = [
  'image/jpeg',
  'image/png',
  'image/webp',
  'application/pdf',
];

const fileFilter = (
  req: Request,
  file: Express.Multer.File,
  cb: multer.FileFilterCallback,
) => {
  if (allowedMimeTypes.includes(file.mimetype)) cb(null, true);
  else cb(new Error('Tipo de archivo no permitido'));
};

const storage = multer.diskStorage({
  destination: (req, file, cb) =>
    cb(null, path.join(process.cwd(), 'uploads', 'secure')),
  filename: (req, file, cb) => {
    const uniqueSuffix = Date.now() + '-' + Math.round(Math.random() * 1e9);
    const ext = path.extname(file.originalname);
    cb(null, `file-${uniqueSuffix}${ext}`);
  },
});

const upload = multer({
  storage,
  fileFilter,
  limits: { fileSize: 5 * 1024 * 1024 },
});
```

## Security Best Practices

### Essential Do's

- Always validate and sanitize user inputs
- Use HTTPS in production with proper security headers
- Implement rate limiting and CORS with specific origins
- Log security events and monitor for suspicious activity
- Store files outside web root with secure filenames
- Use environment variables for all secrets
- Keep dependencies updated and scan for vulnerabilities

### Critical Don'ts

- Don't expose sensitive information in error messages
- Don't use wildcard CORS in production
- Don't trust client-side validation alone
- Don't commit secrets to version control
- Don't store files in web-accessible directories
- Don't skip input validation or ignore security warnings
